Norma Mngoma withdraws state capture inquiry testimony. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The state capture inquiry will now issue a summons to compel Norma Mngoma to testity. Mngoma, the wife of former finance minister Malusi Gigaba has withdrawn her participation at the inquiry. WATCH: Norma Mngoma withdraws state capture inquiry testimony She was due to give evidence on Tuesday afternoon. Her attorney, Gcwalisile Makhathini read a letter to the commission, explaining why Mngoma decided not to testify before the inquiry.